# Testing Coverage Standards - AUTHORITATIVE

## 🚨 **MANDATORY: Single Source of Truth**

**PRIMARY AUTHORITY**: [03-testing-strategy.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/03-testing-strategy.mdc)

**This rule exists to prevent documentation inconsistencies discovered on 2025-11-18.**

---

## ✅ **CORRECT Testing Coverage Standards for Kubernaut**

### **MANDATORY Percentages (Microservices Architecture)**

```markdown
- **Unit Tests**: >=80% of unit-testable code coverage (ALL unit-testable BRs)
- **Integration Tests**: >=80% of integration-testable code coverage (microservices coordination)
- **E2E Tests**: >=80% of full service code coverage (critical user journeys)
- **All Tiers**: >=80% merged (line-by-line dedup across all tiers)
```

### **Why >=80% Per-Tier Coverage is Required**

Kubernaut's microservices architecture requires high per-tier test coverage for:
- ✅ **CRD-based coordination** between 10+ services
- ✅ **Watch-based status propagation** (difficult to unit test)
- ✅ **Owner reference lifecycle management**
- ✅ **Cross-service error handling**
- ✅ **Service discovery and communication patterns**

Coverage is measured **per tier against the tier-specific code subset** (see `scripts/coverage/coverage_report.py`).

**Authoritative Source**: [03-testing-strategy.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/03-testing-strategy.mdc)

---

## ❌ **INCORRECT Standards to AVOID**

### **Old/Monolithic Standards (DO NOT USE)**

```markdown
❌ Unit Tests: 70% (flat, not per-tier)
❌ Integration Tests: <20% or 20% or >50%  ← WRONG: must be >=80% of integration-testable code
❌ E2E Tests: <10% or 10-15%  ← WRONG: must be >=80% of full service code
```

**Why This is Wrong**:
- ❌ Based on monolithic application patterns or outdated flat percentages
- ❌ Does not measure per-tier against tier-specific code subsets
- ❌ Insufficient for CRD controller testing requirements
- ❌ Inadequate for watch-based patterns and K8s API testing

